SIMPLE: wamble
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wamble
<hw>Wam"ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Dan.
<ets>vamle</ets>, and <ets>vammel</ets> squeamish, ready to vomit, Icel.
<ets>v⟦ae⟧ma</ets> to feel nausea, <ets>v⟦ae⟧minn</ets> nauseous.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To heave; to be disturbed by nausea; -- said of the
stomach.</def> <rj><au>L'Estrange.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To move irregularly to and fro; to roll.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wamble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wamble
<hw>Wam"ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Disturbance of the stomach; a
feeling of nausea.</def> <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wamble-cropped</ent>⟦br⟧
